// @run
// @log 1
// @log 2
// @log 3
// @info unreachable: the preceding `is` arms are exhaustive
// DEAD-ARM LINT (B17): once an `is`-chain already exhausts its union, a trailing
// `else` is unreachable — the prior arms cover every input. Reuses
// `conditionsExhaust` (the same exhaustiveness check the no-`else` return path
// uses) to flag the dead `else` as an `info` (greyed, never fails a build). Only
// fires when the chain is provably exhaustive WITHOUT the `else`; a chain that
// still needs the `else` to cover its last variant is left alone.
function classify(v: "a" | "b" | 1): i32 {
  if v is "a" { return 1 } else if v is "b" { return 2 } else if v is 1 {
    return 3
  } else { return 0 }
}
print(classify("a"))  // 1
print(classify("b"))  // 2
print(classify(1))    // 3
